# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev. This file is not sent to the browser.
# Used by Vite’s dev server only: appends ?key= when proxying /api/gemini → Google Gemini API.

GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Alternative name (either works):
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# --- Production (Vercel) ---
# In Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables, add:
#   GEMINI_API_KEY   (or GOOGLE_API_KEY) — same as above; never use VITE_ for secrets.
#   VITE_GEMINI_BASE_URL=/api/gemini
# so the static build calls the serverless proxy in /api/gemini/* (see api/gemini/[...path].ts).
#
# Local production-style test (optional):
# VITE_GEMINI_BASE_URL=/api/gemini

# Optional: model id for “Fill from metrics” (default: gemini-2.5-flash).
# If you see “high demand” errors while quotas look fine, try e.g.:
# VITE_GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite
